cli/output/theme_load.go exports LoadCustomTheme(dir string) (Theme, error). Reads dir/.drift/theme.xml. Parses &lt;theme&gt;&lt;element id="X" color="Y" bold="true|false" dim="true|false"/&gt;...&lt;/theme&gt; using encoding/xml. Requires all 14 element IDs present; returns an error naming the first missing element if any are absent. Returns (Theme{}, os.ErrNotExist) if the file does not exist — caller treats this as "no custom theme, use built-in". The returned Theme has Name="custom". See <ref spec="output.custom_theme">custom theme</ref>.